  "prompt": "How do I save an answer on Quora?",
  "response": "To save an answer on Quora, you can follow these steps:\n\n1. **Log into your Quora account**: Make sure you're signed in to your Quora account.\n\n2. **Find the answer you want to save**: Navigate to the question and locate the specific answer you wish to save.\n\n3. **Use the 'Save' option**: Below the answer, there should be a \"Save\" button (which may appear as a bookmark icon). Click on this button to save the answer.\n\n4. **View saved answers**: To view your saved answers later, go to your profile and look for the section labeled \"Saved\". Here, you will find all the answers you've saved for easy access.\n\nBy following these steps, you can easily keep track of answers you find useful or want to revisit later.",
